This release sees improved alignment to NCI thesaurus. Note the URLs
for NCI cross-references have changed from the deprecated
symbolic-name style to use of numeric fragments. See [1149](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1149) for details.

Additionally this release incorporates multiple additional
relationships and new terms in various anatomical systems,
particularly the nervous system.

![song-learning pathway](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Birdbrain.svg/360px-Birdbrain.svg.png)

# Ontology Diff Report

 * xrefs
    * Adding expansion for NCIT. [1149](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1149)
    * Adding missing NCIt xrefs. [1149](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1149)
    * xref fixes from [CatherineLeroy](https://github.com/CatherineLeroy) [1150](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1150)
    * Switch to using meaning-free numeric NCIT IDs. Confirmed with Gilberto that this is correct. Fixes [1149](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1149)
 * musculoskeletal and connective tissue
    * Adding stroma syn to mammary connective tissue. Fixes [1151](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1151)
    * added explicit skeletal muscle classification. [1154](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1154)
    * made all quadriceps femoris (including vastus lateralis) skeletal, Fixes [1152](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1152)
    * relabeled ocular region to orbital region [1132](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1132)
 * neuro
    * Additional work on hippocampus layers, see https://github.com/obophenotype/mammalian-phenotype-ontology/issues/2110
    * brain mods
    * made S1 part_of parietal cortex (more specific than lobe). Issue [1147](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1147)
    * NT: HVC (Aves). Fixes https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/12057
    * NTs for grouping layers and fields of hippocampus
 * other
    * urinary bladder never in Aves. Fixes [454](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/454)
    * merging adrenal into suprarenal. https://github.com/obophenotype/mouse-anatomy-ontology/issues/110
    * Adding syns for outer limiting membrane pending https://github.com/obophenotype/mammalian-phenotype-ontology/issues/2109#issuecomment-141523542
    * NT: seminal clot.
    * Adding notes to mandibular lymph nodes, consider merging mandibular and submandibular
    * made all medial and laterals disjoint. Should prevent any future occurrences of errors such as in [1138](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1138)
    * Fixed relationship for medial pterygoid that was causing incorrect classification. Fixes [1138](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1138)
    * ciliary nerves, ganglia; submandibular regions

### Changes for: [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702)

 * _Deleted_
    *  **-** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)* [http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Eyelash](http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Eyelash)
    *  **-** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* An eyelash or simply lash is one of the hairs that grow at the edge of the eyelid. Eyelashes protect the eye from debris and perform some of the same function as whiskers do on a cat or a mouse in the sense that they are sensitive to being touched, thus providing a warning that an object is near the eye (which is then closed reflexively). The greek word for eyelash is 'blepharis'. This word is often used as a root in biological terms { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyelash](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyelash) } 
 * _Added_
    *  **+** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)* [C32576](http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C32576)
    *  **+** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* Any of the hairs that grow at the edge of the upper or lower eyelid. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=MGI:anna } 
    *  **+** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[function notes](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000009)* eyelashes protect the eye from debris and are sensitive to touch, thus providing a warning that an object is near the eye (which is then closed reflexively)
    *  **+** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[has exact synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym)* eyelid cilium
    *  **+** [eyelash](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001702) *[has related synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym)* eyelid cilia { [has synonym type](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasSynonymType)=[plural term](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#PLURAL) }

    *  **-** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* An epithelium that is part of a choroid plexus [Automatically generated definition]. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=OBOL:automatic } 
    *  **-** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[has exact synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym)* chorioid plexus of cerebral hemisphere epithelial tissue { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=OBOL:automatic } 
    *  **-** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[has exact synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym)* chorioid plexus of cerebral hemisphere epithelium { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=OBOL:automatic } 
    *  **-** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[has exact synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym)* epithelium of chorioid plexus of cerebral hemisphere { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=OBOL:automatic }

    *  **+** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)* [C42079](http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C42079)
    *  **+** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* The epithelial component of the choroid plexus. Consists of cuboidal epithelial cells surrounding a core of capillaries and loose connective tissue. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choroid_plexus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choroid_plexus) , [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=UBERON:cjm } 
    *  **+** [choroid plexus epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003911) *[structure notes](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000010)* The CP epithelial layer is continuous with the ependymal cell layer that lines the ventricles, but unlike the ependyma, the epithelial layer has tight gap junctions between the cells on the side facing the ventricle (apical surface). These gap junctions prevent the majority of substances from crossing the cell layer into the CSF; thus the CP acts as a bloodCSF barrier

### Changes for: [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058)

 * _Deleted_
    *  **-** [ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) **SubClassOf** [parasympathetic ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001808)
    *  **-** [ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* The ciliary ganglion is a parasympathetic ganglion located in the posterior orbit. It measures 1P2 millimeters in diameter and contains approximately 2,500 neurons (adapted from Wikipedia) { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=NIFSTD:nlx_anat_100304 } 
    *  **-** [ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[label](http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label)* ciliary ganglion
 * _Added_
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) **EquivalentTo** [parasympathetic ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001808) **and** [extends fibers into](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#extends_fibers_into) **some** [oculomotor nerve](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001643) **and** [extends fibers into](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#extends_fibers_into) **some** [short ciliary nerve](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0022302)
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) **SubClassOf** [extends fibers into](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#extends_fibers_into) **some** [short ciliary nerve](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0022302)
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) **SubClassOf** [ganglion of ciliary nerve](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0035783)
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) **SubClassOf** [part of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) **some** [orbital region](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004088)
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[curator notes](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000232)* the main ciliary ganglion (typically just called the ciliary ganglion) is differentiated from the accessory by connection to the oculomotor nerve.
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* A parasympathetic ganglion located in the posterior orbit that contains preganglionic nerves and postganglionic neurons of the oculomotor nerve, connects to the Edinger-Westphal nucleus via the oculomotor nerve and the eye muscles via the short ciliary nerve. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ciliary_ganglion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ciliary_ganglion) , [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=UBERON:cjm } 
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[has exact synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym)* ciliary ganglion { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=MA:0001136 } 
    *  **+** [main ciliary ganglion](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002058) *[label](http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label)* main ciliary ganglion

    *  **-** [eye trabecular meshwork](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0005969) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* A fenestrated endothelial-like tissue situated at the intersection of the cornea and the iris[GO]. The trabecular meshwork is an area of tissue in the eye located around the base of the cornea, near the ciliary body, and is responsible for draining the aqueous humor from the eye via the anterior chamber (the chamber on the front of the eye covered by the cornea). The tissue is spongy and lined by trabeculocytes; it allows fluid to drain into a set of tubes called Schlemm's canal flowing into the blood system[WP].
